# Prisma and Database Discipline

## Schema Changes

Any schema change must include:

- a migration
- updates to docs/PRODUCT.md if domain model changed
- updates to docs/ARCHITECTURE.md if storage changed

## Modeling Conventions

- Use consistent ID strategy (UUID or cuid — do not mix).
- Include createdAt and updatedAt where appropriate.
- Large file blobs must live in S3, not Postgres.

## Indexing

Add indexes for:

- slug lookups
- user ownership (userId)
- foreign keys used in list endpoints

## ID Strategy

- All primary keys must use UUID.
- Prisma model definition:

  id String @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid

- Do not mix ID strategies across core entities.
- Do not use cuid.
- Do not use autoincrement integers for domain entities.


## Raw SQL

- Prefer Prisma client.
- If raw SQL is required:
  - isolate in repository layer
  - document why
